The paper deals with the study of properties of Boolean functions on the hypercube, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The focus is on linear-invariant properties, which are often studied in the context of property testing. The paper specifically deals with matroid freeness properties, which are a subclass of linear-invariant properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
